
Function: ZILCLOSE

Syntax:   (ZILCLOSE file1 arg2)

 file1 (required, evaluated) - a file name.
 arg2  (required, evaluated) - a fixnum.

Returns:

 NIL, after closing the file specified by file1.  The type of file
 access is determined by arg2.

Processing:

 See CLOSE for processing.

 arg2 is a fixnum that determines the type of file access.  Its contents
 are system-dependent.

Errors signaled:

 See CLOSE for errors.

Notes:

 This function underlies CLOSE.

 See member $FILE for more information on file names.

Examples:

 ; None.  Use CLOSE, not this internal function whose processing of
 ; arg2 could change at any time.

